@@ -0,0 +1,46 @@
+# ADR-0002 — Three parallel-isolatable pure-utility modules in src/lib
+
+- Status: Accepted
+- Date: 2026-05-27
+- Relates to: ADR-0001 (test harness + pure-logic coverage)
+
+## Context
+
+`src/lib` already holds small, pure, dependency-free helpers (`cn.ts`, `format.ts`).
+The project is Next.js 16 / React 19 / TypeScript-strict, ESM (`"type": "module"`),
+`moduleResolution: bundler`.
+
+Three new utilities were requested, deliberately designed **file-disjoint** so they
+can be implemented in parallel worktrees and merged with zero conflicts. The only
+shared surface is `package.json` test wiring (owned by ADR-0001) — a one-time edit,
+not a per-module dependency.
+
+## Decision
+
+Add three independent modules, each its own file plus its own colocated `*.test.ts`,
+with **no cross-imports** between them:
+
+1. `src/lib/slug.ts` — `slugify(text)`: lowercase → trim → collapse `[^a-z0-9]+`
+   into a single hyphen → strip edge hyphens. **ASCII-only by design** (accents act
+   as separators, not transliterated; `Café` → `caf`).
+2. `src/lib/num.ts` — `clamp(value, min, max)` (inclusive; ±Infinity snaps to a
+   bound; `NaN` value → `NaN`; non-finite or inverted bound throws `RangeError`) and
+   `roundTo(value, decimals)` (exponential-reparse to beat binary FP so
+   `1.005 → 1.01`; non-finite value unchanged; negative/non-finite decimals → 0).
+3. `src/lib/str.ts` — `truncate(text, max, ellipsis='…')` (ellipsis counted against
+   `max`, result length ≤ `max`) and `titleCase(text)` (first char up / rest down,
+   original whitespace runs preserved).
+
+Tests reuse the ADR-0001 harness: `node --test` via `tsx`, extensionless relative
+imports to satisfy strict `tsc`.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- +24 unit tests, no new framework surface. Suite green (24/24, ~200 ms, Node v24.12.0),
+  `tsc --noEmit` clean.
+- The disjoint design is proven: parallel implement/merge is conflict-free outside the
+  single `package.json` edit.
+- `slugify`'s ASCII-only contract means non-Latin input degrades to separators. If SEO
+  ever needs diacritic folding (`café → cafe`), that is a new, separately scoped task.
+- This run the workspace had reset to an unimplemented state (no `test` script, `tsx`
+  absent, modules missing); the harness and modules were re-established from this ADR.
